Running Pacman:

Running Pacman is simple. Make sure you have about 300-400 KB
of free ram, mostly chip-ram available. The double click the pacman
icon.

Kickstart 2.0+ is highly recommended.


Playing Pacman:

Is simple. Use the joystick to move pacman about and eat all the dots.
Avoid the ghosts and collect bonusses for extra points. The big pills
make you able to eat the ghosts, but only for a short time.

Notes for PAL / NTSC:

Pacman is a PAL-only game. The game screen is too big to fit on 
a NTSC based amiga.

If you own a NTSC amiga with KS2.04 or up, you may be able to get
the screen to display as PAL. ( you need to select PAL mode in
the early startup-screen as well as select a PAL monitor display.
If this does not work, you might try one of the various
'degraders' around, to get a PAL display. )


Pacman options:

On the title screen, you can move the arrows around with the joystick 
and make a selection with the fire button. Since the different difficulty
levels are not fully implemented, it is recommended you only choose
either 'begin' or 'quit'.

Some extra notes:

While playing, pressing fire quits the game.

On easy mode, you get an extra life every 10000 points.
On medium mode you get an extra life at 10000, 30000 and 60000 points.
On hard mode you get an extra life at 60000 points only.

Bonuses:

There are various fruity ( and not so fruity ) bonus items to collect,
for a variety of points. Up to 10000 points can be earned eating these,
so watch out for them!

Removing Pacman:

Pacman does not edit any system resources and does not alter
any system files, nor has it any entry in the system environment.

Pacman can be removed by simply deleting the directory in wich
it was installed.

